'd like some input and any better ideas you can come up with. It's kinda long, and this isn't the entire story, so prepare yourself! :P<br>
<br>
The story begins with a flashback of a man in a jungle. As he is working his way through the thick brush, he notices a rat. Thinking it to be harmless, he continues along his way. However, the rat emits a high-pitched squeak and within moments the man is covered with rats from head to toe. He screams for help, and the bird that was pirched on his shoulder flies off and squawks as loudly as possible. Far away, in a village, a young <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Taksha</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> hears the squawk and runs through the jungle to find his father. He arrives too late - the man has been completely devoured, leaving the half-starving rats still hungry for food. Then, in an instant, all the rats turn into a fine black dust that starts chasing Taksha. He runs as fast as he can, until a man jumps out from the brush to divert the dust. Taksha makes it home safely, but never sees the man again...<br>
<br>
Then we jump ahead. Taksha is now a grown man who searches for relics and artifacts and peddles them to the rich. On his way out to search for more ancient items, he drops by <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Tshakka</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->'s tent. She is an archaeologist employed by the government to search for ancient machinery. (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.silenttransit.com/gallery/tshakka.jpg">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is her character sketch) Taksha tells her that he's heard rumors that there is a buried city to the east, near where his father was killed. He tells her he believes it was called &quot;Times Square&quot;. (no, that's not a corny, planet of the apes-esque plot twist. you'll see the significance.) She wishes him good luck on his trip and he sets off. Moments later, her shovel hits a box, which she digs up and opens to find various trinkets.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, the emperor is in a meeting at the Ministry of History and Literature. They have become aware of the rumors about the buried city and want to see it for themselves. The emperor says that it is the &quot;Final Imprisonment&quot; and that they must send a team immediately. He makes a note to an assistant to fire Tshakka, saying it would be too risky for her to know about the mission (but we have no idea why.)<br>
<br>
Searching through the box at her tent, Tshakka discovers a letter. She opens it and finds that it is addressed &quot;My dearest Tshakka&quot;. The letter is from her father, who died many years ago. She begins to read it.<br>
<br>
It says that many years ago, machinery was used almost incessently to help people. A research company eager to find ways to further use machines to make people's lives easier developed a new type of nanomachine the size of animal cells that could arrange in clouds of various shapes in sizes. For example, the nanomachines could become a chisel, only to reconfigure at command to become a brush. They could even duplicate themselves. The only drawback was that they required living cells for fuel. This was fine for a while, as they were slowly fed plants. But something happened, and one machine became corrupted. It began seeking living animal cells and reproduced very quickly.<br>
<br>
These corrupted cell-machines found their way into the food supply and infected people from the inside, slowly taking over their bodies. Eventually, the entire human race collapsed, and was taken over by these machines. They were called the Darkness and the few survivors made it their lives' mission to take the world back from the machines, and to ensure they were never reawakened. They succeeded for the most part, and people once again became abundant. Darkness outbreaks were few.<br>
<br>
Tshakka is a direct descendant of one the guardians, the letter says, and it is her duty to prevent the Darkness from awakening to cause a major outbreak, just as her father's job was. Then he tells her in the letter that he became infected with the Darkness saving a boy from it in the jungles to the east, and was soon to die. He tells her that all of the remaining Darkness was imprisoned in a buried city to the east, named &quot;Times Square&quot;, and that it is imperative that she prevent it from being discovered.<br>
<br>
<br>
*bum bum bum*<br>
<br>
I'll post the next part of the story, where things really get hairy for Tshakka, a little later. Until then, I'd appreciate any response to what I have so far. <br>
<br>
Thanks! <br>
<br>
