<br>
Just be careful that you don't get too wrapped up with telling all that history you have going and let the character development fall to the wayside. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utenyaku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tenyaku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/28/01 5:39:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> yes, i worried about spending too much time discussing the history, but i can't figure out any other way to get that across... it seems really important to the story.<br>
<br>
*edit: i should add that i really would like to develop Taksha a lot, as he is technically just as important as Tshakka, but i'm trying to condense all of this into the size of a comic book (~30 pages). also, a really big plot twist will happen to him, so the reader needs to have developed a deep sympathy for him. i really need to figure out how to eliminate the chatter about the history of the dust.*<br>
<br>
and yeah, i should have known darkness would be taken. what else could i use... *ponder ponder*<br>
<br>
also, thanks for your feedback. it probably took forever to read that :P<br>
<br>
-ten <p><a href='http://www.silenttransit.com'><img src='http://www.silenttransit.com/button.jpg'></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utenyaku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tenyaku</A> at: 12/28/01 5:44:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udarkora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Twilight Oracle</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/28/01 6:31:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.darkora.net/img/external/dark.jpg width=80 length=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> Took forever to read?  Not really...when you write a lot of short stories and scripts, you have to read them to proofread them (and even though I'm not the fastest reader out there, reading's part of the game...research, proofreading, reviews, critiques, and then all the fun stuff out there to read too).<br>
<br>
I think your idea is a bit much for a single book if you want to develop both characters really well; however, comics do provide a good format for taking shorcuts.  Place your characters in some carefully crafted situations that make the key parts of their personalities stand out.  Also remember that every time your character utters a word of dialogue, let their personality come across (the words they choose, how they say it, how they carry themselves when they say it, etc). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/30/01 12:25:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> It's pretty interesting...<br>
I like it...but comics need dialogue and action as well...<br>
thats where character stuff comes in...<br>
I guess I'm just retyping what darkora said...<br>
but I'd avoid sticking it in one book...when you've got the story mapped out write a script...<br>
a page is usually at the most 9 panels...and you need some action and some dialogue to carry the story...the art will take care of the action but to convey how characters think you'll need dialogue...<br>
with just what you've got I can see more than one book <p><pre>
--
%) Picasso Smilie
---               
Single Handedly saving the porn industry
--
I'm a little out of wack...
If you happen to have any extra whack please contact me...
Thank you
--
</pre></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utenyaku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tenyaku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/30/01 8:07:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> I totally agree. I talked it over with DarkOra, and he gave me a great idea. The story will be split into 4 books - each of the first three will develop one of the characters and give their motives for wanting to go to the city to find the nanomachines. For example, there will be a book just about Tshakka, describing how she discovers the box and stuff. There will also be a great deal of character development, lots more than there was here (I was trying to make it as short as possible)<br>
<br>
Finally, the fourth book is when they all meet, which has the main climax and the resolution. It'll be fun! :P<br>
<br>
-ten <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandxduke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrandxDuke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/30/01 9:30:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> Actually you might want to make sure that the comic isn't to word oriented.  The last thing I like to do is read a comic that is full of word boxes that in turn is full of small type explainging a complex history.<br>
<br>
I'm a patient man, so where I don't like to do that I probally would anyways in the end.  My point is other people wouldn't want to becasue the story is &quot;boring&quot;.<br>
<br>
So, my suggestion is to think of a way to have you characters doing something, may it be exploreing the jungle for &quot;time square&quot;, and have something like falsh backs or other character encounters that force the initial person to explain why they are here.<br>
<br>
The thing is you have a lot of history to give and it would be a bad idea to give it to the reader all at one time.  IMO it would be best to give it to the reader a little at a time.  Make the reader curious why the hero is doing what he/she is doing and curious to what exactly the past is like.<br>
<br>
Though, I do like your concept and story idea.  The end result can be very good if the story is told right. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandxduke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrandxDuke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/30/01 9:31:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utenyaku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tenyaku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/30/01 1:10:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I've pretty much revamped everything and I figured out a way to get around that.<br>
<br>
The first book, the book of Taksha, will focus on Taksha's life and will look into his relationship with Tshakka a little. A major chunk of it will also be him looking for Times Square.<br>
<br>
The second book, the book of the emperor (as of yet unnamed), will mainly focus on the brighter side of the history of the darkness, giving the reader a glimpse at why the nanomachines were originally so useful, and as such, why he wants them. I haven't figured out the meat of this book though, since that will only take a few pages. It will probably mainly consist of the emperor's troops looking for Times Square (with lots of action as they fight off beasts in the jungles). Also, this book will probably take a closer look at Taksha and Tshakka.<br>
<br>
The third book, the book of Tshakka, focuses deeply on her relationship with Taksha at the beginning. Then the focus changes to the darker side of the darkness when she discovers that box with the letter from her father, so the reader learns the second half of the history. Then, she takes off to find Times Square before anyone else.<br>
<br>
Finally, the fourth book will begin when they all meet at the final imprisonment of the darkness, and the chaos that results. My secret for now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Does anyone have any ideas for the second book? It's very important to everything else, but I've still got to figure out the meat of the story for that book.<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
<br>
-ten <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utenyaku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tenyaku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/30/01 1:18:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=437.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story synopsis - The Darkness</span><hr size=1> I was thinking, for a name, The Guardians sounds kinda cool. I'm sure it's taken though... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
